Interface EntityIdentifier<O,J>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AllowableOutputParameterType<J>, AllowableParameterType<J>, DomainType<J>, DomainTypeDescriptor<J>, ExpressableType<J>, Navigable<J>, Serializable, Type<J>, Writeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EntityIdentifierComposite<O,J>, EntityIdentifierCompositeAggregated<O,J>, EntityIdentifierCompositeNonAggregated<O,J>, EntityIdentifierSimple<O,J>

    public interface EntityIdentifier<O,J>
extends Navigable<J>, AllowableOutputParameterType<J>
    Descriptor for an entity's identifier
    "To Do:"
    (6.0) : drop SingularPersistentAttribute from extends list only 2 out of the 3 identifier forms is a SingularPersistentAttribute, the 3rd is the "non-aggregated cid" form. Granted we could model the 3rd as a VirtualPersistentAttribute (or a VirtualNavigable) but the underlying issue is the abstract base class (AbstractSingularPersistentAttribute) and what we can pass to its ctor - ideally we'd pass the boot-model form (PersistentAttributeMapping) which does not exist for this 3rd id form.

        Get a SingularPersistentAttribute representation of the identifier.

        Note that for the case of a non-aggregated composite identifier this returns a "virtual" attribute mapping (VirtualPersistentAttribute)

      • resolveHydratedState

        default Object resolveHydratedState(Object hydratedForm,
                                    ExecutionContext executionContext,
                                    SharedSessionContractImplementor session,
                                    Object containerInstance)
        Given a hydrated representation of this Readable, resolve its domain representation.

        E.g. for a composite, the hydrated form is an Object[] representing the "simple state" of the composite's attributes. Resolution of those values returns the instance of the component with its resolved values injected.
